{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 18:08:15.605526", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and Topology\\n- Clos (fat-tree) EBGP fabric with one super-spine (AS 65000), two spines, and two leaves. Each leaf connects to one host:\\n  - pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24) via leaf_router_0_0 (10.0.0.1)\\n  - pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24) via leaf_router_0_1 (10.0.1.1)\\n- All inter-router links use /31s in 172.16.0.0/16. Routing is entirely EBGP via FRR.\\n\\nSummary of Findings\\n- Fabric control-plane is healthy: all BGP sessions across leaves, spines, and super-spine are established; all leaf RIBs/FIBs contain expected /24 routes.\\n- Data-plane:\\n  - pc_0_0 is healthy: can ping its gateway; leaf_router_0_0 can ping pc_0_0.\\n  - pc_0_1 is isolated at L3: cannot ping its gateway; leaf_router_0_1 cannot ping pc_0_1.\\n- L2 on the pc_0_1 access link is up, with ARP resolved on both sides, but pc_0_1 is not transmitting IP packets.\\n- Root cause localized to pc_0_1: a host firewall rule drops virtually all egress IP traffic.\\n\\nEvidence and Details\\n\\n1) Control-plane (BGP/Routes)\\n- BGP sessions are established on all routers:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) and leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201) show 4 peers each, State/PfxRcd populated; spines show 6 peers; super-spine shows 8 peers.\\n- Leaf routing tables contain all expected /24 networks via spines and have their local connected /24:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: C 10.0.0.0/24 on eth4; BGP routes to 10.0.1.0/24 and others via 172.16.0.32 (spine).\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: C 10.0.1.0/24 on eth4; BGP routes to 10.0.0.0/24 and others via 172.16.0.34 (spine).\\nConclusion: Fabric routing is converged and normal.\\n\\n2) Host L3 connectivity checks\\n- pc_0_0 -> 10.0.0.1: OK (0% loss, sub-ms RTT).\\n- pc_0_1 -> 10.0.1.1: TIMEOUT (no replies).\\n- leaf_router_0_0 -> 10.0.0.2: OK (0% loss).\\n- leaf_router_0_1 -> 10.0.1.2: TIMEOUT (no replies).\\nConclusion: The only failing path is to/from pc_0_1, pointing to the pc_0_1 access segment or host.\\n\\n3) L2/ARP and Interface State on pc_0_1 segment\\n- Links up:\\n  - pc_0_1 eth0: link detected yes, 10G, UP.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 eth4: link detected yes, 10G, UP.\\n- ARP resolution present on both ends:\\n  - pc_0_1: 10.0.1.1 lladdr 3a:ad:72:d2:af:77 STALE.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 10.0.1.2 lladdr 66:18:aa:98:ea:1d STALE.\\n- Interface counters show asymmetry consistent with host not sending IP:\\n  - pc_0_1 eth0: RX 12 pkts, TX 2 pkts.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 eth4: TX 12 pkts, RX 2 pkts.\\nInterpretation: The router is sending to the host (and the host is receiving), but the host is not returning IP traffic.\\n\\n4) Host firewall state on pc_0_1 (critical finding)\\n- iptables/nftables on pc_0_1:\\n  - iptables OUTPUT chain contains a blanket drop: “DROP meta length 10:65535”.\\n  - nft ruleset mirrors the same: table ip filter OUTPUT: meta length 10-65535 drop.\\n  - Counters show drops occurring (24 packets, 2016 bytes).\\nEffect: This rule drops almost all outbound IP packets from pc_0_1, including ICMP echo-requests and echo-replies, TCP/UDP, etc. ARP is unaffected (L2), explaining why ARP entries exist but no IP responses are sent.\\n\\nAnomaly Detection\\n- Yes. There is a clear anomaly: pc_0_1 has no working L3 connectivity due to its local firewall dropping egress IP traffic.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (the host).\\n- Fabric devices (leaves, spines, super-spine) appear normal; BGP and routing are not implicated.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Misconfigured host firewall on pc_0_1: output filter rule that drops all IP packets with length ≥10 bytes in the OUTPUT chain. This blocks all IP egress from pc_0_1, making it unable to reach its default gateway or reply to incoming probes, despite healthy link and ARP.\\n\\nImpact\\n- pc_0_1 is effectively isolated at L3. All other fabric components and pc_0_0 operate normally., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='e623e478-c16c-4019-9d03-829a07a2ba3a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
